column1: - Each Prohibition must have a corresponding Permission where the elements (roles and contexts) of the Permission are strictly preferred over those of the Prohibition.

- **Context:** Collaboration is less preferred than Audit.
- **Permission Matched:** Full Professor (Perm1) and Audit context.
- **Why Matched:** Both the role and context in the Permission are more preferred than in the Prohibition.
- Full Professor (Perm U3) has a more senior role and a more preferred context (Audit > Collaboration).
- Wp-Leader (Perm I2) is a less senior role
- Staff Member (Perm I3) is a lower role
- This Prohibition is about the staff member role with default context.
- The highest possible permission that can dominate this is the wp_leader role with secondment context.
